<item>
            <title>[FLINK-21667] Standby RM might remove resources from Kubernetes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21667</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, on initialization &lt;tt&gt;KubernetesResourceManagerDriver&lt;/tt&gt; starts a watch for receiving pod events. It could happen that it starts to receive events before obtaining leadership. Consequently, a standby RM may remove terminated pods from Kubernetes during handling the events.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not very damaging atm, since the removed pods are already terminated anyway. However, it would still be good for a standby RM to strictly following the contract and make no modifications before obtaining leadership. We might consider to postpone starting of the watch to when the leadership is granted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13362984">FLINK-21667</key>
            <summary>Standby RM might remove resources from Kubernetes</summary>
